24\ndrwxr-xr-x  2 root root 4096 Apr 11 11:01 AR-025\ndrwxr-xr-x  2 root root 4096 Apr 11 11:21 AR-026\ndrwxr-xr-x  2 root root 4096 Apr 11 11:47 AR-027\ndrwxr-xr-x  2 root root 4096 Apr 11 12:06 AR-028\ndrwxr-xr-x  2 root root 4096 Apr 11 12:28 AR-029\ndrwxr-xr-x  2 root root 4096 Apr 11 12:57 AR-030\ndrwxr-xr-x  2 root root 4096 Apr 11 13:17 AR-031\ndrwxr-xr-x  2 root root 4096 Apr 11 13:38 AR-032\ndrwxr-xr-x  2 root root 4096 Apr 11 13:56 AR-033\ndrwxr-xr-x  2 root root 4096 Apr 11 14:26 AR-034\ndrwxr-xr-x  2 root root 4096 Apr 11 14:50 AR-035\ndrwxr-xr-x  2 root root 4096 Apr 11 15:17 AR-036\ndrwxr-xr-x  2 root root 4096 Apr 11 15:44 AR-037\ndrwxr-xr-x  2 root root 4096 Apr 11 16:13 AR-038\ndrwxr-xr-x  2 root root 4096 Apr 11 16:44 AR-039\ndrwxr-xr-x  2 root root 4096 Apr 11 17:35 AR-040\ndrwxr-xr-x  2 root root 4096 Apr 11 17:55 AR-041\ndrwxr-xr-x  2 root root 4096 Apr 11 18:36 AR-042\ndrwxr-xr-x  2 root root 4096 Apr 11 19:08 AR-043\n","exit":0,"description":"List changes directory","truncated":false},"title":"List changes directory","time":{"start":1775905763471,"end":1775905763508}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775905763514,"sessionID":"ses_283c4cff2ffeChbK0U2GIzk9f2","part":{"id":"prt_d7c3b6ea700144R15A1FLOQB2V","messageID":"msg_d7c3b4f5a001LvaGk2f1OVLt7H","sessionID":"ses_283c4cff2ffeChbK0U2GIzk9f2","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-7d29fa283d364410af5c9d3f8f5cd6de","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-041/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-041/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-041 — E2E 集成测试\n2: \n3: ## 概述\n4: \n5: | 属性 | 值 |\n6: |------|-----|\n7: | AR | AR-041 |\n8: | Module | test/e2e |\n9: | Language | Go |\n10: | Size | L |\n11: \n12: ---\n13: \n14: ## 1. Purpose (目的)\n15: \n16: 为 AgentCube 系统建立完整的 E2E 集成测试框架，确保：\n17: \n18: - **系统级验证**：验证 WorkloadManager、Router、PicoD、Agentd 四大组件在真实 Kubernetes 环境中的集成工作流\n19: - **CRD 生命周期测试**：验证 `AgentRuntime` 和 `CodeInterpreter` CRD 的完整生命周期（创建→运行→删除）\n20: - **API 端点集成**：验证各组件 HTTP API 端点在真实集群中的正确交互（Health、Sandbox CRUD、Invocation Proxy）\n21: - **Session 路由验证**：验证 Router 正确解析/创建 Session 并反向代理到 Sandbox Pod\n22: - **Python SDK 集成**：验证 Python SDK (`agentcube-sdk`) 与真实控制平面和数据平面的交互\n23: - **client-go 验证**：验证生成的 Kubernetes client-go 代码对 CRD 的正确操作能力\n24: - **回归测试基准**：建立稳定的 E2E 测试基准，确保后续迭代不破坏集成行为\n25: \n26: ---\n27: \n28: ## 2. Scope (范围)\n29: \n30: ### 2.1 In Scope\n31: \n32: | Deliverable | Description |\n33: |-------------|-------------|\n34: | E2E 测试框架搭建 | 使用 Kind 创建本地 Kubernetes 集群，编写 Go E2E 测试套件 |\n35: | WorkloadManager E2E 测试 | 验证 `/health`、`POST /v1/agent-runtime`、`POST /v1/code-interpreter`、`DELETE /v1/*/sessions/:sessionId` 端点 |\n36: | Router E2E 测试 | 验证 `/health/live`、`/health/ready`、Invocation Proxy 路由、Session Header 传递、JWT 签名注入 |\n37: | PicoD E2E 测试 | 验证 `/health`、`POST /api/execute`（命令执行）、`POST /api/files`（文件上传）、`GET /api/files`（文件列表）、`GET /api/files/*path`（文件下载）、JWT 认证 |\n38: | Agentd E2E 测试 | 验证 Idle Cleanup Controller 在真实集群中的 Leader Election 和资源清理行为 |\n39: | CRD 生命周期 E2E | 验证 AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter CRD 创建、Pod 启动、状态更新、资源删除的完整流程 |\n40: | client-go E2E | 验证 `client-go` 生成的 typed client、informer、lister 对 CRD 的 CRUD 操作 |\n41: | Python SDK E2E | 验证 `CodeInterpreterClient` 和 `AgentRuntimeClient` 与真实 Router/WorkloadManager 的交互 |\n42: | E2E 测试脚本增强 | 增强 `run_e2e.sh` 支持并行测试、日志收集、失败诊断、超时控制 |\n43: | 测试配置管理 | 提供 Kind 集群配置、测试命名空间隔离、测试数据清理机制 |\n44: \n45: ### 2.2 Out of Scope\n46: \n47: | Item | Reason |\n48: |------|--------|\n49: | 性能/压力测试 | 本 AR 关注功能验证，性能测试属于独立专项 |\n50: | Chaos Engineering | 故障注入测试超出本 AR 范围，后续专项处理 |\n51: | 多集群/跨 namespace 复杂场景 | 初始 E2E 覆盖单集群单 namespace，复杂场景后续迭代 |\n52: | Volcano Scheduler 集成测试 | Volcano 为可选组件，本 AR 聚焦核心 AgentCube 功能 |\n53: | TLS/mTLS 验证 | TLS 配置为可选特性，基础 E2E 使用 HTTP |\n54: | GPU/特殊硬件场景 | 硬件依赖场景需专用环境，本 AR 使用标准 Kind 集群 |\n55: \n56: ---\n57: \n58: ## 3. Impact Analysis (影响分析)\n59: \n60: ### 3.1 新增文件\n61: \n62: | File | Description |\n63: |------|-------------|\n64: | `test/e2e/e2e_test.go` | E2E 测试入口，测试套件注册、Suite 初始化/清理 |\n65: | `test/e2e/workloadmanager_test.go` | WorkloadManager API 端点 E2E 测试（Health、Sandbox CRUD） |\n66: | `test/e2e/router_test.go` | Router Session 路由、Invocation Proxy、JWT E2E 测试 |\n67: | `test/e2e/picod_test.go` | PicoD 命令执行、文件操作、JWT 认证 E2E 测试 |\n68: | `test/e2e/agentd_test.go` | Agentd Idle Cleanup Controller E2E 测试 |\n69: | `test/e2e/crd_lifecycle_test.go` | AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter CRD 完整生命周期 E2E 测试 |\n70: | `test/e2e/clientgo_test.go` | client-go typed client/informer/lister E2E 测试 |\n71: | `test/e2e/python_sdk_test.go` | Python SDK 与真实服务交互的 E2E 测试（通过 subprocess 调用 pytest） |\n72: | `test/e2e/framework/suite.go` | E2E 测试框架：Kind 集群管理、Helm 部署、Client 初始化 |\n73: | `test/e2e/framework/kind.go` | Kind 集群创建/删除、镜像加载工具函数 |\n74: | `test/e2e/framework/helm.go` | Helm chart 安装/升级/卸载工具函数 |\n75: | `test/e2e/framework/client.go` | Kubernetes client、HTTP client、Redis client 初始化 |\n76: | `test/e2e/framework/wait.go` | Pod/CRD/Service 就绪等待工具函数 |\n77: | `test/e2e/framework/cleanup.go` | 测试资源清理工具函数 |\n78: | `test/e2e/fixtures/testdata.go` | 测试数据 fixtures（CRD templates、JWT keys、测试文件） |\n79: | `test/e2e/python_tests/test_e2e_code_interpreter.py` | Python SDK CodeInterpreter E2E pytest 测试 |\n80: | `test/e2e/python_tests/test_e2e_agent_runtime.py` | Python SDK AgentRuntime E2E pytest 测试 |\n81: | `test/e2e/python_tests/conftest.py` | Python E2E pytest 配置和 fixtures |\n82: \n83: ### 3.2 修改文件\n84: \n85: | File | Change |\n86: |------|--------|\n87: | `test/e2e/run_e2e.sh` | 增强：并行测试支持、更完善的日志收集、失败诊断输出、超时控制参数化 |\n88: | `test/e2e/kind-config.yaml` | 增强：添加 Redis/Valkey 部署配置、支持多节点测试场景 |\n89: | `Makefile` | 新增 `e2e-parallel`、`e2e-router-only`、`e2e-workloadmanager-only` 等细粒度目标 |\n90: | `go.mod` | 新增 E2E 测试依赖：`sigs.k8s.io/e2e-framework`、`github.com/docker/docker` 等 |\n91: | `sdk-python/pyproject.toml` | 新增 E2E pytest 配置 marker `@pytest.mark.e2e` |\n92: \n93: ### 3.3 Upstream Dependencies\n94: \n95: | Dependency | Purpose |\n96: |------------|---------|\n97: | `sigs.k8s.io/e2e-framework` | Kubernetes E2E 测试框架（Suite、Feature、Step 抽象） |\n98: | `sigs.k8s.io/kind` | 本地 Kubernetes 集群创建工具 |\n99: | `helm.sh/helm/v3` | Helm chart 部署工具（Go SDK） |\n100: | `k8s.io/client-go` | Kubernetes API 客户端（已有，用于 CRD 操作） |\n101: | `github.com/stretchr/testify` | Go 测试断言库（已有） |\n102: | `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9` | Redis client（用于 Session Store 验证） |\n103: | `github.com/docker/docker` | Docker client（用于镜像构建/加载验证） |\n104: | `pytest>=7.4.0` | Python E2E 测试框架 |\n105: | `requests>=2.28.0` | Python HTTP client（Python SDK 已依赖） |\n106: \n107: ### 3.4 Downstream Consumers\n108: \n109: | Consumer | Usage |\n110: |----------|-------|\n111: | CI/CD Pipeline | 在 PR 合入前运行 E2E 测试验证集成质量 |\n112: | 开发团队 | 本地运行 E2E 验证完整系统行为 |\n113: | Release 流程 | 版本发布前执行 E2E 确保稳定性 |\n114: | 用户文档 | E2E 测试结果作为系统行为验证文档 |\n115: \n116: ---\n117: \n118: ## 4. Alternatives Considered (备选方案)\n119: \n120: ### 4.1 使用 Ginkgo + Gomega 而非 sigs.k8s.io/e2e-framework\n121: \n122: **优点**：\n123: - Ginkgo 是 Kubernetes 生态广泛使用的 BDD 测试框架\n124: - Gomega 提供丰富的断言和异步匹配器\n125: - 与现有 Kubernetes controller-runtime 测试风格一致\n126: \n127: **缺点**：\n128: - `e2e-framework` 提供更高级的 Suite/Feature/Step 抽象，专为 Kubernetes E2E 设计\n129: - `e2e-framework` 内置 Kind 集群管理、Helm 部署、等待机制\n130: - Ginkgo 需要更多自定义基础设施代码\n131: \n132: **决策**：采用 `sigs.k8s.io/e2e-framework`，利用其 Kubernetes 专用抽象简化 E2E 测试编写\n133: \n134: ### 4.2 使用 minikube 而非 Kind\n135: \n136: **优点**：\n137: - minikube 支持更多 Kubernetes 版本和驱动\n138: - minikube 有更丰富的 addon 系统\n139: \n140: **缺点**：\n141: - Kind 启动更快、资源消耗更低\n142: - Kind 更适合 CI 环境（无 hypervisor 依赖）\n143: - 项目已使用 Kind（`run_e2e.sh` 已有 Kind 配置）\n144: \n145: **决策**：继续使用 Kind，保持与现有脚本一致\n146: \n147: ### 4.3 Python SDK E2E 独立为单独仓库\n148: \n149: **优点**：\n150: - Python 测试可独立演进\n151: - 减少主仓库测试依赖复杂度\n152: \n153: **缺点**：\n154: - 需要额外仓库维护\n155: - Python SDK 与 Go 服务紧密耦合，需同一环境验证\n156: - CI 配置分散，协调成本增加\n157: \n158: **决策**：Python SDK E2E 测试保持在 `test/e2e/python_tests/`，通过 subprocess 调用 pytest，统一 E2E 环境\n159: \n160: ### 4.4 真实生产集群 E2E vs Kind 本地集群\n161: \n162: **优点（真实集群）**：\n163: - 更接近生产环境\n164: - 可验证真实网络/存储配置\n165: \n166: **缺点**：\n167: - 需要专用集群资源\n168: - 测试环境隔离复杂\n169: - 测试运行成本高\n170: - CI 环境难以配置\n171: \n172: **决策**：使用 Kind 本地集群进行 E2E，真实集群验证通过专项环境测试\n173: \n174: ### 4.5 使用 Kuttl 进行 E2E 测试\n175: \n176: **优点**：\n177: - Kuttl 专为 Kubernetes CRD 测试设计\n178: - YAML 驱动的测试声明式风格\n179: - 内置步骤序列和断言\n180: \n181: **缺点**：\n182: - Kuttl 主要面向 YAML 场景测试\n183: - 对 HTTP API 测试支持较弱\n184: - 与 Router/PicoD HTTP API 测试需要额外工具\n185: - Go 测试更灵活支持复杂逻辑\n186: \n187: **决策**：使用 Go E2E 测试框架，提供更灵活的 HTTP API 和复杂场景验证能力\n188: \n189: ---\n190: \n191: ## 5. Risks\n192: \n193: | Risk | Mitigation |\n194: |------|------------|\n195: | Kind 集群启动失败影响 CI | 增加 Kind 环境检测和降级策略，提供 `SKIP_KIND_SETUP` 环境变量跳过集群创建 |\n196: | E2E 测试运行时间过长影响 CI 效率 | 使用测试分组和并行运行，提供 `E2E_TEST_GROUP` 选择性运行 |\n197: | 测试资源泄漏导致集群状态污染 | 使用 namespace 隔离，每个测试 Suite 实现 cleanup hook |\n198: | Docker 镜像构建失败导致 E2E 无法运行 | 增加镜像预构建缓存，提供 `USE_PREBUILT_IMAGES` 使用预构建镜像 |\n199: | Redis 连接失败导致 Session Store 测试失败 | 在 Kind 集群中部署 Redis，增加 Redis 就绪等待检查 |\n200: | JWT key 未正确生成导致 PicoD 认证失败 | 在测试框架中生成测试 JWT key pair，确保正确注入 |\n201: | Python SDK E2E subprocess 调用失败 | 增加 pytest 返回码检查和日志捕获，失败时输出详细诊断 |\n202: | 并发测试导致资源争用 | 使用资源锁和顺序测试关键路径，并发仅用于独立场景 |\n203: | 测试环境差异导致结果不稳定 | 固定 Kind 集群配置，使用确定性测试数据 |\n204: \n205: ---\n206: \n207: ## 6. Implementation Checklist\n208: \n209: - [ ] 创建 `test/e2e/framework/` 目录结构\n210: - [ ] 实现 `framework/suite.go` - E2E Suite 初始化和清理\n211: - [ ] 实现 `framework/kind.go` - Kind 集群创建/删除/镜像加载\n212: - [ ] 实现 `framework/helm.go` - Helm chart 安装/卸载工具\n213: - [ ] 实现 `framework/client.go` - K8s/HTTP/Redis client 初始化\n214: - [ ] 实现 `framework/wait.go` - Pod/CRD/Service 就绪等待\n215: - [ ] 实现 `framework/cleanup.go` - 测试资源清理\n216: - [ ] 实现 `fixtures/testdata.go` - 测试数据 fixtures\n217: - [ ] 创建 `test/e2e/e2e_test.go` - E2E 测试入口\n218: - [ ] 实现 `workloadmanager_test.go` - Health/Sandbox CRUD E2E 测试\n219: - [ ] 实现 `router_test.go` - Session 路由/Invocation Proxy E2E 测试\n220: - [ ] 实现 `picod_test.go` - 命令执行/文件操作/JWT 认证 E2E 测试\n221: - [ ] 实现 `agentd_test.go` - Idle Cleanup Controller E2E 测试\n222: - [ ] 实现 `crd_lifecycle_test.go` - AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter 生命周期 E2E\n223: - [ ] 实现 `clientgo_test.go` - client-go typed client/informer/lister E2E\n224: - [ ] 创建 `test/e2e/python_tests/` 目录\n225: - [ ] 实现 `python_tests/conftest.py` - Python E2E pytest 配置\n226: - [ ] 实现 `python_tests/test_e2e_code_interpreter.py` - Python SDK CodeInterpreter E2E\n227: - [ ] 实现 `python_tests/test_e2e_agent_runtime.py` - Python SDK AgentRuntime E2E\n228: - [ ] 增强 `run_e2e.sh` - 并行测试、日志收集、失败诊断\n229: - [ ] 增强 `kind-config.yaml` - Redis 部署配置\n230: - [ ] 更新 `Makefile` - 新增细粒度 E2E 目标\n231: - [ ] 更新 `go.mod` - 新增 E2E 测试依赖\n232: - [ ] 运行完整 E2E 测试套件验证所有组件集成\n233: - [ ] 在 CI 中配置 E2E 测试运行\n234: \n235: ---\n236: \n237: ## 7. References\n238: \n239: - [Deployment Specification](../../deployment/spec.md)\n240: - [Sandbox Orchestration Specification](../../sandbox-orchestration/spec.md)\n241: - [Session Routing Specification](../../session-routing/spec.md)\n242: - [Code Execution (PicoD) Specification](../../code-execution/spec.md)\n243: - [Python SDK Specification](../../python-sdk/spec.md)\n244: - [client-go Library Spec](../deployment/client-go.md)\n245: - [Design Document](../../design.md)\n246: - sigs.k8s.io/e2e-framework: https://pkg.go.dev/sigs.k8s.io/e2e-framework\n247: - Kind Documentation: https://kind.sigs.k8s.io/\n248: - Helm Documentation: https://helm.sh/docs/\n249: - Kubernetes E2E Testing Best Practices: https://github.com/kubernetes/community/blob/master/contributors/devel/sig-testing/e2e-tests.md\n\n(End of file - total 249 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-041 — E2E 集成测试\n\n## 概述\n\n| 属性 | 值 |\n|------|-----|\n| AR | AR-041 |\n| Module | test/e2e |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | L |\n\n---\n\n## 1. Purpose (目的)\n\n为 AgentCube 系统建立完整的 E2E 集成测试框架，确保：\n\n- **系统级验证**：验证 WorkloadManager、Router、PicoD、Agentd 四大组件在真实 Kubernetes 环境中的集成工作流\n- **CRD 生命周期测试**：验证 `AgentRuntime` 和 `CodeInterpreter` CRD 的完整生命周期（创建→运行→删除）\n- **API 端点集成**：验证各组件 HTTP API 端点在真实集群中的正确交互（Health、Sandbox CRUD、Invocation Proxy）","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-041/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775905763467,"end":1775905763511}}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775905763546,"sessionID":"ses_283c4cff2ffeChbK0U2GIzk9f2","part":{"id":"prt_d7c3b70b90014eR2CNWqnxtpap","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d7c3b4f5a001LvaGk2f1OVLt7H","sessionID":"ses_283c4cff2ffeChbK0U2GIzk9f2","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":21050,"input":18385,"output":206,"reasoning":0,"cache":{"write":0,"read":2459}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775905766564,"sessionID":"ses_283c4cff2ffeChbK0U2GIzk9f2","part":{"id":"prt_d7c3b7ca1001VhwsRjo1EzPkTb","messageID":"msg_d7c3b70f2001O5d84Ntn5Z9RP6","sessionID":"ses_283c4cff2ffeChbK0U2GIzk9f2","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775905770888,"sessionID":"ses_283c4cff2ffeChbK0U2GIzk9f2","part":{"id":"prt_d7c3b8d5e001zSgT5YXFU3Z7zj","messageID":"msg_d7c3b70f2001O5d84Ntn5Z9RP6","sessionID":"ses_283c4cff2ffeChbK0U2GIzk9f2","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-0a272020326b4bbc99d8e72c746e786f","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-019: CLI Binary Entry Points (4 Binaries)\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: This module defines the CLI binary entry points for the agentcube system, consisting of four main executables:\n6: \n7: | Binary | Purpose | Module | HTTP Framework |\n8: |--------|---------|--------|----------------|\n9: | `picod` | Local code execution daemon | `pkg/picod` | Gin |\n10: | `router` | Session routing and reverse proxy | `pkg/router` | Gin |\n11: | `workloadmanager` | Workload manager HTTP server | `pkg/workloadmanager` | Chi |\n12: | `agentd` | Agent daemon (idle cleanup controller) | `pkg/agentd` | controller-runtime |\n13: \n14: ---\n15: \n16: ## Architecture\n17: \n18: ### Directory Structure\n19: \n20: ```\n21: cmd/\n22: ├── picod/\n23: │   ├── main.go              # PicoD entry point (implemented)\n24: │   └── doc.go               # Package documentation\n25: ├── router/\n26: │   ├── main.go              # Router entry point\n27: │   └── doc.go               # Package documentation\n28: ├── workloadmanager/\n29: │   ├── main.go              # WorkloadManager entry point\n30: │   └── doc.go               # Package documentation\n31: └── agentd/\n32: │   ├── main.go              # Agentd entry point\n33: │   └── doc.go               # Package documentation\n34: ```\n35: \n36: ### Binary Dependency Graph\n37: \n38: ```\n39: ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n40: │                            CLI Binaries                                       │\n41: ├──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n42: │                                                                               │\n43: │   ┌───────────┐     ┌───────────┐     ┌───────────────┐     ┌───────────┐   │\n44: │   │   picod   │     │   router  │     │workloadmanager│     │  agentd   │   │\n45: │   └───────────┘     └───────────┘     └───────────────┘     └───────────┘   │\n46: │        │                 │                     │                   │        │\n47: │        ▼                 ▼                     ▼                   ▼        │\n48: │   ┌───────────┐     ┌───────────┐     ┌───────────────┐     ┌───────────┐   │\n49: │   │ pkg/picod │     │pkg/router │     │pkg/workload   │     │pkg/agentd │   │\n50: │   │           │     │           │     │   manager     │     │           │   │\n51: │   └───────────┘     └───────────┘     └───────────────┘     └───────────┘   │\n52: │        │                 │                     │                   │        │\n53: │        ▼                 ▼                     ▼                   ▼        │\n54: │   ┌───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐ │\n55: │   │                    Common Dependencies                                 │ │\n56: │   │  - k8s.io/klog/v2 (logging)                                           │ │\n57: │   │  - github.com/spf13/pflag (flags)                                     │ │\n58: │   │  - context, os, signal                                                │ │\n59: │   └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘ │\n60: │                                                                               │\n61: └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n62: ```\n63: \n64: ### Deployment Model\n65: \n66: ```\n67: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n68: │                      Kubernetes Cluster                          │\n69: ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n70: │                                                                  │\n71: │  ┌──────────────────┐    ┌──────────────────┐                  │\n72: │  │ router Deployment│    │workloadmanager   │                  │\n73: │  │    (Pod :8080)   │───▶│ Deployment       │                  │\n74: │  └──────────────────┘    │   (Pod :8080)    │                  │\n75: │           │              └──────────────────┘                  │\n76: │           │                      │                              │\n77: │           ▼                      ▼                              │\n78: │  ┌──────────────────┐    ┌──────────────────┐                  │\n79: │  │ Redis/Valkey     │    │  K8s API Server  │                  │\n80: │  │ (Session Store)  │    │  (CRDs, Pods)    │                  │\n81: │  └──────────────────┘    └──────────────────┘                  │\n82: │                                                                  │\n83: │  ┌──────────────────┐                                           │\n84: │  │ agentd Deployment│    (Leader Election enabled)             │\n85: │  │  (Controller)    │                                           │\n86: │  └──────────────────┘                                           │\n87: │                                                                  │\n88: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n89: \n90: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n91: │                      Sandbox Pod                                 │\n92: ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n93: │  ┌──────────────────┐                                           │\n94: │  │ picod sidecar    │    (Local code execution)                │\n95: │  │   (Port 8080)    │                                           │\n96: │  └──────────────────┘                                           │\n97: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n98: ```\n99: \n100: ---\n101: \n102: ## Data Structures\n103: \n104: ### Common CLI Configuration Pattern\n105: \n106: ```go\n107: package main\n108: \n109: type CLIConfig struct {\n110:     LogLevel    string `flag:\"log-level\" default:\"info\" usage:\"Log level (debug, info, warn, error)\"`\n111:     MetricsAddr string `flag:\"metrics-addr\" default:\"0\" usage:\"Metrics server address (0 to disable)\"`\n112:     HealthAddr  string `flag:\"health-addr\" default:\"\" usage:\"Health check server address\"`\n113: }\n114: ```\n115: \n116: ### PicoD CLI Configuration\n117: \n118: ```go\n119: package main\n120: \n121: type PicoDConfig struct {\n122:     CLIConfig\n123:     Port         int    `flag:\"port\" default:\"8080\" usage:\"HTTP listening port\"`\n124:     Workspace    string `flag:\"workspace\" default:\"\" usage:\"Workspace directory path\"`\n125:     AuthEnabled  bool   `flag:\"auth-enabled\" default:\"true\" usage:\"Enable authentication\"`\n126:     MaxExecTime  int    `flag:\"max-exec-time\" default:\"30\" usage:\"Maximum execution time in seconds\"`\n127:     MaxFileSize  int64  `flag:\"max-file-size\" default:\"10485760\" usage:\"Maximum file size in bytes\"`\n128:     SanitizeRoot string `flag:\"sanitize-root\" default:\"\" usage:\"Root directory for path sanitization\"`\n129: }\n130: ```\n131: \n132: ### Router CLI Configuration\n133: \n134: ```go\n135: package main\n136: \n137: type RouterConfig struct {\n138:     CLIConfig\n139:     Port                 string `flag:\"port\" default:\":8080\" usage:\"HTTP listening port\"`\n140:     MaxConcurrentRequests int   `flag:\"max-concurrent\" default:\"1000\" usage:\"Maximum concurrent requests\"`\n141:     Debug                bool   `flag:\"debug\" default:\"false\" usage:\"Enable debug mode\"`\n142:     EnableTLS            bool   `flag:\"enable-tls\" default:\"false\" usage:\"Enable TLS\"`\n143:     TLSCert              string `flag:\"tls-cert\" default:\"\" usage:\"TLS certificate file\"`\n144:     TLSKey               string `flag:\"tls-key\" default:\"\" usage:\"TLS key file\"`\n145:     StoreAddr            string `flag:\"store-addr\" default:\"\" usage:\"Redis/Valkey address\"`\n146:     StorePassword        string `flag:\"store-password\" default:\"\" usage:\"Redis/Valkey password\"`\n147:     StoreType            string `flag:\"store-type\" default:\"redis\" usage:\"Store type (redis, valkey)\"`\n148: }\n149: ```\n150: \n151: ### WorkloadManager CLI Configuration\n152: \n153: ```go\n154: package main\n155: \n156: type WorkloadManagerConfig struct {\n157:     CLIConfig\n158:     Addr              string        `flag:\"addr\" default:\":8080\" usage:\"HTTP server address\"`\n159:     ReadTimeout       time.Duration `flag:\"read-timeout\" default:\"30s\" usage:\"HTTP read timeout\"`\n160:     WriteTimeout      time.Duration `flag:\"write-timeout\" default:\"30s\" usage:\"HTTP write timeout\"`\n161:     IdleTimeout       time.Duration `flag:\"idle-timeout\" default:\"90s\" usage:\"HTTP idle timeout\"`\n162:     ShutdownTimeout   time.Duration `flag:\"shutdown-timeout\" default:\"10s\" usage:\"Graceful shutdown timeout\"`\n163:     GCInterval        time.Duration `flag:\"gc-interval\" default:\"5m\" usage:\"Garbage collection interval\"`\n164:     GCOnceTimeout     time.Duration `flag:\"gc-once-timeout\" default:\"30s\" usage:\"Single GC run timeout\"`\n165:     Kubeconfig        string        `flag:\"kubeconfig\" default:\"\" usage:\"Kubernetes config file path\"`\n166:     MasterURL         string        `flag:\"master-url\" default:\"\" usage:\"Kubernetes API server URL\"`\n167: }\n168: ```\n169: \n170: ### Agentd CLI Configuration\n171: \n172: ```go\n173: package main\n174: \n175: type AgentdConfig struct {\n176:     CLIConfig\n177:     IdleThreshold        time.Duration `flag:\"idle-threshold\" default:\"30m\" usage:\"Idle threshold for cleanup\"`\n178:     CheckInterval        time.Duration `flag:\"check-interval\" default:\"5m\" usage:\"Cleanup check interval\"`\n179:     MaxConcurrentCleanup int           `flag:\"max-concurrent\" default:\"10\" usage:\"Maximum concurrent cleanups\"`\n180:     Namespaces           []string      `flag:\"namespace\" default:\"default\" usage:\"Namespaces to watch\"`\n181:     LeaderElection       bool          `flag:\"leader-election\" default:\"true\" usage:\"Enable leader election\"`\n182:     LeaderElectionID     string        `flag:\"leader-election-id\" default:\"agentcube-agentd\" usage:\"Leader election ID\"`\n183:     Kubeconfig           string        `flag:\"kubeconfig\" default:\"\" usage:\"Kubernetes config file path\"`\n184: }\n185: ```\n186: \n187: ---\n188: \n189: ## API Contracts\n190: \n191: ### Binary Entry Point Interface\n192: \n193: Each binary follows this pattern:\n194: \n195: ```go\n196: package main\n197: \n198: type Binary interface {\n199:     InitFlags() *Config\n200:     ValidateConfig(cfg *Config) error\n201:     Run(ctx context.Context, cfg *Config) error\n202:     Shutdown(ctx context.Context) error\n203: }\n204: \n205: func main() {\n206:     klog.InitFlags(nil)\n207:     flag.Parse()\n208:     \n209:     cfg := InitFlags()\n210:     if err := ValidateConfig(cfg); err != nil {\n211:         klog.Fatalf(\"invalid config: %v\", err)\n212:         os.Exit(1)\n213:     }\n214:     \n215:     ctx, cancel := signal.NotifyContext(context.Background(), syscall.SIGTERM, syscall.SIGINT)\n216:     defer cancel()\n217:     \n218:     if err := Run(ctx, cfg); err != nil {\n219:         klog.Fatalf(\"run error: %v\", err)\n220:         os.Exit(1)\n221:     }\n222: }\n223: ```\n224: \n225: ### Signal Handling Contract\n226: \n227: ```go\n228: package main\n229: \n230: func setupSignalHandler() context.Context {\n231:     ctx, cancel := context.WithCancel(context.Background())\n232:     \n233:     c := make(chan os.Signal, 2)\n234:     signal.Notify(c, syscall.SIGTERM, syscall.SIGINT)\n235:     \n236:     go func() {\n237:         sig := <-c\n238:         klog.InfoS(\"received signal\", \"signal\", sig)\n239:         cancel()\n240:         \n241:         if sig == syscall.SIGKILL {\n242:             <-c\n243:             klog.InfoS(\"received second signal, forcing exit\")\n244:             os.Exit(1)\n245:         }\n246:     }()\n247:     \n248:     return ctx\n249: }\n250: ```\n251: \n252: ### Health Check Contract\n253: \n254: ```go\n255: package main\n256: \n257: type HealthChecker interface {\n258:     Live() bool\n259:     Ready() bool\n260: }\n261: \n262: func (h *HealthServer) Start(addr string) error {\n263:     mux := http.NewServeMux()\n264:     mux.HandleFunc(\"/live\", func(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n265:         if h.Live() {\n266:             w.WriteHeader(http.StatusOK)\n267:             w.Write([]byte(\"OK\"))\n268:         } else {\n269:             w.WriteHeader(http.StatusServiceUnavailable)\n270:         }\n271:     })\n272:     mux.HandleFunc(\"/ready\", func(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n273:         if h.Ready() {\n274:             w.WriteHeader(http.StatusOK)\n275:             w.Write([]byte(\"OK\"))\n276:         } else {\n277:             w.WriteHeader(http.StatusServiceUnavailable)\n278:         }\n279:     })\n280:     return http.ListenAndServe(addr, mux)\n281: }\n282: ```\n283: \n284: ### Flag Registration Contract\n285: \n286: ```go\n287: package main\n288: \n289: func InitFlags() *Config {\n290:     cfg := &Config{}\n291:     \n292:     klog.InitFlags(nil)\n293:     flag.Set(\"logtostderr\", \"true\")\n294:     \n295:     flag.StringVar(&cfg.LogLevel, \"log-level\", \"info\", \"Log level\")\n296:     flag.StringVar(&cfg.MetricsAddr, \"metrics-addr\", \"0\", \"Metrics address\")\n297:     flag.StringVar(&cfg.HealthAddr, \"health-addr\", \"\", \"Health address\")\n298:     \n299:     flag.Parse()\n300:     \n301:     return cfg\n302: }\n303: ```\n304: \n305: ---\n306: \n307: ## Binary Implementation Details\n308: \n309: ### 1. picod (cmd/picod/main.go)\n310: \n311: **Purpose**: Local code execution daemon running as a sidecar in sandbox pods.\n312: \n313: **Current Implementation** (pkg/picod/server.go:26-77):\n314: \n315: ```go\n316: func main() {\n317:     klog.InitFlags(nil)\n318:     flag.Set(\"logtostderr\", \"true\")\n319: \n320:     port := flag.Int(\"port\", 8080, \"HTTP listening port\")\n321:     workspace := flag.String(\"workspace\", \"\", \"Workspace directory path\")\n322:     flag.Parse()\n323: \n324:     config := &picod.Config{\n325:         Port:      *port,\n326:         Workspace: *workspace,\n327:     }\n328: \n329:     server, err := picod.NewServer(config)\n330:     if err != nil {\n331:         klog.Fatalf(\"failed to create server: %v\", err)\n332:         os.Exit(1)\n333:     }\n334: \n335:     if err := server.Run(context.Background()); err != nil {\n336:         klog.Fatalf(\"server error: %v\", err)\n337:         os.Exit(1)\n338:     }\n339: }\n340: ```\n341: \n342: **Endpoints**:\n343: | Path | Method | Purpose |\n344: |------|--------|---------|\n345: | `/health` | GET | Health check |\n346: | `/api/execute` | POST | Execute code |\n347: | `/api/files` | POST | Upload file |\n348: | `/api/files` | GET | List files |\n349: | `/api/files/*path` | GET | Download file |\n350: \n351: ### 2. router (cmd/router/main.go)\n352: \n353: **Purpose**: Session routing and reverse proxy for agent/code interpreter invocations.\n354: \n355: **Implementation Template**:\n356: \n357: ```go\n358: func main() {\n359:     klog.InitFlags(nil)\n360:     flag.Set(\"logtostderr\", \"true\")\n361:     \n362:     cfg := &RouterConfig{}\n363:     flag.StringVar(&cfg.Port, \"port\", \":8080\", \"HTTP listening port\")\n364:     flag.StringVar(&cfg.StoreAddr, \"store-addr\", \"\", \"Redis/Valkey address\")\n365:     flag.StringVar(&cfg.StoreType, \"store-type\", \"redis\", \"Store type\")\n366:     flag.IntVar(&cfg.MaxConcurrentRequests, \"max-concurrent\", 1000, \"Max concurrent requests\")\n367:     flag.BoolVar(&cfg.Debug, \"debug\", false, \"Enable debug mode\")\n368:     flag.Parse()\n369:     \n370:     ctx := setupSignalHandler()\n371:     \n372:     store, err := initStore(cfg)\n373:     if err != nil {\n374:         klog.Fatalf(\"failed to init store: %v\", err)\n375:     }\n376:     \n377:     sessionManager := router.NewSessionManager(store)\n378:     jwtManager := router.NewJWTManager()\n379:     \n380:     server := router.NewServer(&router.Config{\n381:         Port:                 cfg.Port,\n382:         MaxConcurrentRequests: cfg.MaxConcurrentRequests,\n383:         Debug:                cfg.Debug,\n384:     }, sessionManager, store, jwtManager, klog.Logger{})\n385:     \n386:     if err := server.Start(ctx); err != nil {\n387:         klog.Fatalf(\"router error: %v\", err)\n388:     }\n389: }\n390: ```\n391: \n392: **Endpoints**:\n393: | Path | Method | Purpose |\n394: |------|--------|---------|\n395: | `/health/live` | GET | Liveness probe |\n396: | `/health/ready` | GET | Readiness probe |\n397: | `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/agent-runtimes/:name/invocations/*path` | GET/POST | Agent invocation proxy |\n398: | `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/code-interpreters/:name/invocations/*path` | GET/POST | Code interpreter proxy |\n399: \n400: ### 3. workloadmanager (cmd/workloadmanager/main.go)\n401: \n402: **Purpose**: Workload manager HTTP server for sandbox lifecycle management.\n403: \n404: **Implementation Template**:\n405: \n406: ```go\n407: func main() {\n408:     klog.InitFlags(nil)\n409:     flag.Set(\"logtostderr\", \"true\")\n410:     \n411:     cfg := &WorkloadManagerConfig{}\n412:     flag.StringVar(&cfg.Addr, \"addr\", \":8080\", \"HTTP server address\")\n413:     flag.DurationVar(&cfg.ReadTimeout, \"read-timeout\", 30*time.Second, \"Read timeout\")\n414:     flag.DurationVar(&cfg.WriteTimeout, \"write-timeout\", 30*time.Second, \"Write timeout\")\n415:     flag.DurationVar(&cfg.GCInterval, \"gc-interval\", 5*time.Minute, \"GC interval\")\n416:     flag.StringVar(&cfg.Kubeconfig, \"kubeconfig\", \"\", \"Kubeconfig path\")\n417:     flag.Parse()\n418:     \n419:     ctx := setupSignalHandler()\n420:     \n421:     k8sClient, err := workloadmanager.NewK8sClient(cfg.Kubeconfig, cfg.MasterURL)\n422:     if err != nil {\n423:         klog.Fatalf(\"failed to create k8s client: %v\", err)\n424:     }\n425:     \n426:     store, err := initStore(cfg)\n427:     if err != nil {\n428:         klog.Fatalf(\"failed to init store: %v\", err)\n429:     }\n430:     \n431:     server := workloadmanager.NewHTTPServerWithClients(\n432:         workloadmanager.Config{\n433:             Addr:            cfg.Addr,\n434:             ReadTimeout:     cfg.ReadTimeout,\n435:             WriteTimeout:    cfg.WriteTimeout,\n436:             ShutdownTimeout: cfg.ShutdownTimeout,\n437:         },\n438:         klog.Logger{},\n439:         k8sClient,\n440:         store,\n441:     )\n442:     \n443:     server.RegisterHandler(\"health\", workloadmanager.NewHealthHandler())\n444:     server.RegisterHandler(\"sandbox\", workloadmanager.NewSandboxHandler(k8sClient, store))\n445:     \n446:     server.GracefulShutdown()\n447:     \n448:     errCh := server.Start()\n449:     select {\n450:     case err := <-errCh:\n451:         klog.Fatalf(\"workloadmanager error: %v\", err)\n452:     case <-ctx.Done():\n453:         server.Stop(context.Background())\n454:     }\n455: }\n456: ```\n457: \n458: **Endpoints**:\n459: | Path | Method | Purpose |\n460: |------|--------|---------|\n461: | `/health/live` | GET | Liveness probe |\n462: | `/health/ready` | GET | Readiness probe |\n463: | `/sandboxes` | POST | Create sandbox |\n464: | `/sandboxes/:id` | GET | Get sandbox |\n465: | `/sandboxes/:id` | DELETE | Delete sandbox |\n466: \n467: ### 4. agentd (cmd/agentd/main.go)\n468: \n469: **Purpose**: Kubernetes controller for idle resource cleanup using controller-runtime.\n470: \n471: **Implementation Template**:\n472: \n473: ```go\n474: func main() {\n475:     klog.InitFlags(nil)\n476:     flag.Set(\"logtostderr\", \"true\")\n477:     \n478:     cfg := &AgentdConfig{}\n479:     flag.DurationVar(&cfg.IdleThreshold, \"idle-threshold\", 30*time.Minute, \"Idle threshold\")\n480:     flag.DurationVar(&cfg.CheckInterval, \"check-interval\", 5*time.Minute, \"Check interval\")\n481:     flag.IntVar(&cfg.MaxConcurrentCleanup, \"max-concurrent\", 10, \"Max concurrent cleanups\")\n482:     flag.BoolVar(&cfg.LeaderElection, \"leader-election\", true, \"Enable leader election\")\n483:     flag.StringVar(&cfg.LeaderElectionID, \"leader-election-id\", \"agentcube-agentd\", \"Leader election ID\")\n484:     flag.Parse()\n485:     \n486:     k8sConfig, err := ctrl.GetConfig()\n487:     if err != nil {\n488:         klog.Fatalf(\"failed to get k8s config: %v\", err)\n489:     }\n490:     \n491:     mgr, err := ctrl.NewManager(k8sConfig, ctrl.Options{\n492:         LeaderElection:          cfg.LeaderElection,\n493:         LeaderElectionID:        cfg.LeaderElectionID,\n494:         LeaderElectionNamespace: \"default\",\n495:     })\n496:     if err != nil {\n497:         klog.Fatalf(\"failed to create manager: %v\", err)\n498:     }\n499:     \n500:     if err := agentd.SetupIdleCleanupController(mgr, cfg); err != nil {\n501:         klog.Fatalf(\"failed to setup controller: %v\", err)\n502:     }\n503:     \n504:     klog.InfoS(\"starting agentd controller\")\n505:     if err := mgr.Start(ctrl.SetupSignalHandler()); err != nil {\n506:         klog.Fatalf(\"controller error: %v\", err)\n507:     }\n508: }\n509: ```\n510: \n511: ---\n512: \n513: ## Error Handling\n514: \n515: ### Error Categories\n516: \n517: | Category | Description | Action |\n518: |----------|-------------|--------|\n519: | `ErrConfigInvalid` | Configuration validation failure | Log fatal, exit 1 |\n520: | `ErrStoreConnect` | Store connection failure | Log fatal, exit 1 |\n521: | `ErrK8sConnect` | Kubernetes connection failure | Log fatal, exit 1 |\n522: | `ErrServerStart` | HTTP server start failure | Log fatal, exit 1 |\n523: | `ErrSignalReceived` | Graceful shutdown triggered | Log info, cancel context |\n524: | `ErrShutdownTimeout` | Shutdown exceeded timeout | Log warning, force exit |\n525: \n526: ### Error Handling Pattern\n527: \n528: ```go\n529: func handleStartupError(component string, err error) {\n530:     if errors.Is(err, context.Canceled) {\n531:         klog.InfoS(\"shutdown requested\")\n532:         return\n533:     }\n534:     \n535:     if errors.Is(err, syscall.SIGTERM) || errors.Is(err, syscall.SIGINT) {\n536:         klog.InfoS(\"received termination signal\", \"signal\", err)\n537:         return\n538:     }\n539:     \n540:     klog.ErrorS(err, \"startup failure\", \"component\", component)\n541:     os.Exit(1)\n542: }\n543: ```\n544: \n545: ### Graceful Shutdown Sequence\n546: \n547: ```\n548: 1. Signal received (SIGTERM/SIGINT)\n549: 2. Cancel main context\n550: 3. Stop accepting new requests\n551: 4. Wait for in-flight requests (timeout configurable)\n552: 5. Close store connections\n553: 6. Close K8s client connections\n554: 7. Exit with code 0\n555: ```\n556: \n557: ### Validation Errors\n558: \n559: ```go\n560: func ValidateConfig(cfg *Config) error {\n561:     if cfg.Port <= 0 || cfg.Port > 65535 {\n562:         return fmt.Errorf(\"invalid port: %d\", cfg.Port)\n563:     }\n564:     \n565:     if cfg.IdleThreshold < 0 {\n566:         return fmt.Errorf(\"invalid idle threshold: %v\", cfg.IdleThreshold)\n567:     }\n568:     \n569:     if cfg.CheckInterval < 0 {\n570:         return fmt.Errorf(\"invalid check interval: %v\", cfg.CheckInterval)\n571:     }\n572:     \n573:     if cfg.MaxConcurrentCleanup < 0 {\n574:         return fmt.Errorf(\"invalid max concurrent cleanup: %d\", cfg.MaxConcurrentCleanup)\n575:     }\n576:     \n577:     return nil\n578: }\n579: ```\n580: \n581: ---\n582: \n583: ## Testing Strategy\n584: \n585: ### Unit Tests\n586: \n587: #### Flag Parsing Tests\n588: \n589: ```go\n590: func TestInitFlags(t *testing.T) {\n591:     tests := []struct {\n592:         name     string\n593:         args     []string\n594:         expected *Config\n595:     }{\n596:         {\n597:             name: \"default values\",\n598:             args: []string{},\n599:             expected: &Config{\n600:                 Port:           8080,\n601:                 LogLevel:       \"info\",\n602:                 IdleThreshold:  30 * time.Minute,\n603:             },\n604:         },\n605:         {\n606:             name: \"custom port\",\n607:             args: []string{\"-port\", \"9000\"},\n608:             expected: &Config{\n609:                 Port:          9000,\n610:             },\n611:         },\n612:         {\n613:             name: \"multiple flags\",\n614:             args: []string{\"-port\", \"9000\", \"-debug\", \"true\"},\n615:             expected: &Config{\n616:                 Port:  9000,\n617:                 Debug: true,\n618:             },\n619:         },\n620:     }\n621:     \n622:     for _, tt := range tests {\n623:         t.Run(tt.name, func(t *testing.T) {\n624:             fs := flag.NewFlagSet(\"test\", flag.ContinueOnError)\n625:             cfg := &Config{}\n626:             setupFlags(fs, cfg)\n627:             \n628:             err := fs.Parse(tt.args)\n629:             require.NoError(t, err)\n630:             \n631:             assert.Equal(t, tt.expected.Port, cfg.Port)\n632:         })\n633:     }\n634: }\n635: ```\n636: \n637: #### Signal Handler Tests\n638: \n639: ```go\n640: func TestSignalHandler(t *testing.T) {\n641:     ctx := setupSignalHandler()\n642:     \n643:     syscall.Kill(syscall.Getpid(), syscall.SIGTERM)\n644:     \n645:     select {\n646:     case <-ctx.Done():\n647:         assert.True(t, true)\n648:     case <-time.After(5 * time.Second):\n649:         t.Fatal(\"signal handler did not cancel context\")\n650:     }\n651: }\n652: ```\n653: \n654: #### Config Validation Tests\n655: \n656: ```go\n657: func TestValidateConfig(t *testing.T) {\n658:     tests := []struct {\n659:         name        string\n660:         config      *Config\n661:         expectError bool\n662:     }{\n663:         {\n664:             name: \"valid config\",\n665:             config: &Config{\n666:                 Port:          8080,\n667:                 IdleThreshold: 30 * time.Minute,\n668:             },\n669:             expectError: false,\n670:         },\n671:         {\n672:             name: \"invalid port\",\n673:             config: &Config{\n674:                 Port: -1,\n675:             },\n676:             expectError: true,\n677:         },\n678:         {\n679:             name: \"invalid idle threshold\",\n680:             config: &Config{\n681:                 IdleThreshold: -1 * time.Minute,\n682:             },\n683:             expectError: true,\n684:         },\n685:     }\n686:     \n687:     for _, tt := range tests {\n688:         t.Run(tt.name, func(t *testing.T) {\n689:             err := ValidateConfig(tt.config)\n690:             if tt.expectError {\n691:                 assert.Error(t, err)\n692:             } else {\n693:                 assert.NoError(t, err)\n694:             }\n695:         })\n696:     }\n697: }\n698: ```\n699: \n700: ### Integration Tests\n701: \n702: #### Binary Startup Tests\n703: \n704: ```go\n705: func TestBinaryStartup(t *testing.T) {\n706:     if testing.Short() {\n707:         t.Skip(\"skipping integration test\")\n708:     }\n709:     \n710:     binary := buildBinary(t, \"picod\")\n711:     \n712:     cmd := exec.Command(binary, \"-port\", \"18080\")\n713:     cmd.Stdout = &bytes.Buffer{}\n714:     cmd.Stderr = &bytes.Buffer{}\n715:     \n716:     err := cmd.Start()\n717:     require.NoError(t, err)\n718:     \n719:     defer cmd.Process.Kill()\n720:     \n721:     assert.Eventually(t, func() bool {\n722:         resp, err := http.Get(\"http://localhost:18080/health\")\n723:         if err != nil {\n724:             return false\n725:         }\n726:         defer resp.Body.Close()\n727:         return resp.StatusCode == http.StatusOK\n728:     }, 10*time.Second, 100*time.Millisecond)\n729: }\n730: ```\n731: \n732: #### Graceful Shutdown Tests\n733: \n734: ```go\n735: func TestGracefulShutdown(t *testing.T) {\n736:     binary := buildBinary(t, \"router\")\n737:     \n738:     cmd := exec.Command(binary, \"-port\", \":18080\", \"-store-type\", \"memory\")\n739:     cmd.Stdout = &bytes.Buffer{}\n740:     cmd.Stderr = &bytes.Buffer{}\n741:     \n742:     err := cmd.Start()\n743:     require.NoError(t, err)\n744:     \n745:     waitForHealthy(t, \"http://localhost:18080/health/live\")\n746:     \n747:     syscall.Kill(cmd.Process.Pid, syscall.SIGTERM)\n748:     \n749:     done := make(chan error, 1)\n750:     go func() {\n751:         done <- cmd.Wait()\n752:     }()\n753:     \n754:     select {\n755:     case err := <-done:\n756:         assert.NoError(t, err)\n757:     case <-time.After(15 * time.Second):\n758:         t.Fatal(\"binary did not shutdown within timeout\")\n759:     }\n760: }\n761: ```\n762: \n763: ### Build Tests\n764: \n765: ```go\n766: func TestBuildAllBinaries(t *testing.T) {\n767:     binaries := []string{\"picod\", \"router\", \"workloadmanager\", \"agentd\"}\n768:     \n769:     for _, binary := range binaries {\n770:         t.Run(binary, func(t *testing.T) {\n771:             cmd := exec.Command(\"go\", \"build\", \"-o\", \"/tmp/\"+binary, \"./cmd/\"+binary)\n772:             output, err := cmd.CombinedOutput()\n773:             assert.NoError(t, err, \"build output: %s\", output)\n774:             \n775:             assert.FileExists(t, \"/tmp/\"+binary)\n776:         })\n777:     }\n778: }\n779: ```\n780: \n781: ---\n782: \n783: ## Metrics\n784: \n785: ### Prometheus Metrics\n786: \n787: ```go\n788: var (\n789:     startupDuration = prometheus.NewGaugeVec(\n790:         prometheus.GaugeOpts{\n791:             Name: \"agentcube_binary_startup_duration_seconds\",\n792:             Help: \"Time taken for binary startup\",\n793:         },\n794:         []string{\"binary\"},\n795:     )\n796:     \n797:     shutdownDuration = prometheus.NewGaugeVec(\n798:         prometheus.GaugeOpts{\n799:             Name: \"agentcube_binary_shutdown_duration_seconds\",\n800:             Help: \"Time taken for graceful shutdown\",\n801:         },\n802:         []string{\"binary\"},\n803:     )\n804:     \n805:     configReloadCount = prometheus.NewCounterVec(\n806:         prometheus.CounterOpts{\n807:             Name: \"agentcube_binary_config_reload_total\",\n808:             Help: \"Number of configuration reloads\",\n809:         },\n810:         []string{\"binary\"},\n811:     )\n812: )\n813: ```\n814: \n815: ---\n816: \n817: ## Configuration\n818: \n819: ### Environment Variables\n820: \n821: | Variable | Binary | Purpose |\n822: |----------|--------|---------|\n823: | `PORT` | picod, router, workloadmanager | HTTP port override |\n824: | `WORKSPACE` | picod | Workspace directory |\n825: | `STORE_ADDR` | router, workloadmanager | Redis/Valkey address |\n826: | `STORE_TYPE` | router, workloadmanager | Store backend type |\n827: | `KUBECONFIG` | workloadmanager, agentd | Kubernetes config path |\n828: | `LOG_LEVEL` | all | Log level override |\n829: \n830: ### Command-Line Flags Summary\n831: \n832: | Flag | Default | Purpose |\n833: |------|---------|---------|\n834: | `-port` | 8080 | HTTP listening port |\n835: | `-workspace` | current dir | Workspace directory (picod) |\n836: | `-idle-threshold` | 30m | Idle cleanup threshold (agentd) |\n837: | `-check-interval` | 5m | Cleanup check interval (agentd) |\n838: | `-leader-election` | true | Enable leader election (agentd) |\n839: | `-kubeconfig` | in-cluster | Kubernetes config path |\n840: | `-debug` | false | Enable debug mode (router) |\n841: | `-metrics-addr` | 0 | Prometheus metrics address |\n842: \n843: ---\n844: \n845: ## Build Configuration\n846: \n847: ### Go Module\n848: \n849: ```go\n850: // go.mod\n851: module github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube\n852: \n853: go 1.24\n854: \n855: require (\n856:     github.com/gin-gonic/gin v1.x\n857:     github.com/go-chi/chi/v5 v5.x\n858:     k8s.io/klog/v2 v2.x\n859:     sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime v0.19.x\n860: )\n861: ```\n862: \n863: ### Makefile Targets\n864: \n865: ```makefile\n866: .PHONY: build clean\n867: \n868: build:\n869: \tgo build -o bin/picod ./cmd/picod\n870: \tgo build -o bin/router ./cmd/router\n871: \tgo build -o bin/workloadmanager ./cmd/workloadmanager\n872: \tgo build -o bin/agentd ./cmd/agentd\n873: \n874: clean:\n875: \trm -rf bin/\n876: \n877: build-picod:\n878: \tgo build -o bin/picod ./cmd/picod\n879: \n880: build-router:\n881: \tgo build -o bin/router ./cmd/router\n882: \n883: build-workloadmanager:\n884: \tgo build -o bin/workloadmanager ./cmd/workloadmanager\n885: \n886: build-agentd:\n887: \tgo build -o bin/agentd ./cmd/agentd\n888: ```\n889: \n890: ### Docker Build\n891: \n892: ```dockerfile\n893: # Dockerfile for picod\n894: FROM golang:1.24-alpine AS builder\n895: WORKDIR /app\n896: COPY . .\n897: RUN go build -o /picod ./cmd/picod\n898: \n899: FROM alpine:3.19\n900: COPY --from=builder /picod /picod\n901: ENTRYPOINT [\"/picod\"]\n902: ```\n903: \n904: ---\n905: \n906: ## Implementation Checklist\n907: \n908: - [x] `cmd/picod/main.go` - PicoD entry point (implemented)\n909: - [ ] `cmd/router/main.go` - Router entry point\n910: - [ ] `cmd/workloadmanager/main.go` - WorkloadManager entry point\n911: - [ ] `cmd/agentd/main.go` - Agentd entry point\n912: - [ ] Common signal handling package\n913: - [ ] Common flag validation utilities\n914: - [ ] Health check server integration\n915: - [ ] Metrics server integration\n916: - [ ] Unit tests for flag parsing\n917: - [ ] Unit tests for config validation\n918: - [ ] Integration tests for binary startup\n919: - [ ] Integration tests for graceful shutdown\n920: - [ ] Makefile build targets\n921: - [ ] Docker build configurations\n922: - [ ] Helm deployment manifests\n923: \n924: ---\n925: \n926: ## Dependencies\n927: \n928: | Package | Version | Purpose |\n929: |---------|---------|---------|\n930: | `k8s.io/klog/v2` | v2.x | Structured logging |\n931: | `github.com/spf13/pflag` | v1.x | POSIX/GNU-style flags |\n932: | `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime` | v0.19.x | Controller utilities (agentd) |\n933: | `github.com/gin-gonic/gin` | v1.x | HTTP framework (picod, router) |\n934: | `github.com/go-chi/chi/v5` | v5.x | HTTP framework (workloadmanager) |\n935: | `github.com/prometheus/client_golang` | v1.x | Metrics |\n\n(End of file - total 935 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-019: CLI Binary Entry Points (4 Binaries)\n\n## Overview\n\nThis module defines the CLI binary entry points for the agentcube system, consisting of four main executables:\n\n| Binary | Purpose | Module | HTTP Framework |\n|--------|---------|--------|----------------|\n| `picod` | Local code execution daemon | `pkg/picod` | Gin |\n| `router` | Session routing and reverse proxy | `pkg/router` | Gin |\n| `workloadmanager` | Workload manager HTTP server | `pkg/workloadmanager` | Chi |\n| `agentd` | Agent daemon (idle cleanup controller) | `pkg/agentd` | controller-runtime |\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Directory Structure\n\n```","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/design.md","time":{"start":1775905770875,"end":1775905770885}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775905770902,"sessionID":"ses_283c4cff2ffeChbK0U2GIzk9f2","part":{"id":"prt_d7c3b86160016T60fdhKao328j","messageID":"msg_d7c3b70f2001O5d84Ntn5Z9RP6","sessionID":"ses_283c4cff2ffeChbK0U2GIzk9f2","type":"tool","tool":"bash","callID":"toolu_tool-e878d4fc53614aa98f3dcad03ebac5eb","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"ls -la changes/AR-043/","description":"List AR-043 directory"},"output":"total 28\ndrwxr-xr-x  2 root root 4096 Apr 11 19:08 .\ndrwxr-xr-x 45 root root 4096 Apr 11 19:08 ..\n-rw-r--r--  1 root root  866 Apr 11 19:08 delta-spec.md\n-rw-r--r--  1 root root 1004 Apr 11 19:08 design.md\n-rw-r--r--  1 root root 1269 Apr 11 19:08 proposal.md\n-rw-r--r--  1 root root  700 Apr 11 19:08 spec.md\n-rw-r--r--  1 root root 1193 Apr 11 19:08 tasks.md\n","metadata":{"output":"total 28\ndrwxr-xr-x  2 root root 4096 Apr 11 19:08 .\ndrwxr-xr-x 45 root root 4096 Apr 11 19:08 ..\n-rw-r--r--  1 root root  866 Apr 11 19:08 delta-spec.md\n-rw-r--r--  1 root root 1004 Apr 11 19:08 design.md\n-rw-r--r--  1 root root 1269 Apr 11 19:08 proposal.md\n-rw-r--r--  1 root root  700 Apr 11 19:08 spec.md\n-rw-r--r--  1 root root 1193 Apr 11 19:08 tasks.md\n","exit":0,"description":"List AR-043 directory","truncated":false},"title":"List AR-043 directory","time":{"start":1775905770867,"end":1775905770901}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775905770907,"sessionID":"ses_283c4cff2ffeChbK0U2GIzk9f2","part":{"id":"prt_d7c3b89e200100q7eoVTuAdVWm","messageID":"msg_d7c3b70f2001O5d84Ntn5Z9RP6","sessionID":"ses_283c4cff2ffeChbK0U2GIzk9f2","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-62cf0804106f41e6afcefb9b1fa61518","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/docs/docs/getting-started/installation.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/docs/docs/getting-started/installation.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: sidebar_position: 1\n3: id: installation\n4: title: Installation\n5: description: Install AgentCube and set up your development environment\n6: ---\n7: \n8: # Installation\n9: \n10: ## Prerequisites\n11: \n12: Before installing AgentCube, ensure you have the following prerequisites:\n13: \n14: ### System Requirements\n15: \n16: - **Operating System**: Linux, macOS, or Windows with WSL2\n17: - **Kubernetes**: v1.24+ cluster (minikube, kind, or production cluster)\n18: - **kubectl**: v1.24+ configured to access your cluster\n19: - **Helm**: v3.8+ (optional, for Helm deployment)\n20: \n21: ### Language-specific Requirements\n22: \n23: For Python SDK:\n24: - Python 3.8+\n25: - pip package manager\n26: \n27: For Go client:\n28: - Go 1.19+\n29: - Go modules enabled\n30: \n31: ### Kubernetes Setup\n32: \n33: Verify your Kubernetes cluster is running:\n34: \n35: ```bash\n36: kubectl cluster-info\n37: kubectl get nodes\n38: ```\n39: \n40: Ensure you have sufficient resources:\n41: - Minimum 2 CPU cores\n42: - 4GB RAM available\n43: - 10GB disk space for sandbox pods\n44: \n45: ## Installation Methods\n46: \n47: ### Option 1: Helm Chart (Recommended)\n48: \n49: Install AgentCube using the official Helm chart:\n50: \n51: ```bash\n52: # Add AgentCube Helm repository\n53: helm repo add agentcube https://volcano-sh.github.io/agentcube/charts\n54: helm repo update\n55: \n56: # Install AgentCube\n57: helm install agentcube agentcube/agentcube \\\n58:   --namespace agentcube-system \\\n59:   --create-namespace \\\n60:   --set image.tag=v0.2.0\n61: ```\n62: \n63: Verify the installation:\n64: \n65: ```bash\n66: kubectl get pods -n agentcube-system\n67: ```\n68: \n69: Expected output:\n70: ```\n71: NAME                         READY   STATUS    RESTARTS   AGE\n72: agentcube-controller-0       1/1     Running   0          2m\n73: agentcube-router-0           1/1     Running   0          2m\n74: ```\n75: \n76: ### Option 2:kubectl Deployment\n77: \n78: Deploy directly using kubectl:\n79: \n80: ```bash\n81: # Apply CRDs\n82: kubectl apply -f https://raw.githubusercontent.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/main/manifests/crds.yaml\n83: \n84: # Deploy AgentCube components\n85: kubectl apply -f https://raw.githubusercontent.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/main/manifests/deployment.yaml \\\n86:   -n agentcube-system\n87: ```\n88: \n89: ### Option 3: Development Build\n90: \n91: For development or testing unreleased features:\n92: \n93: ```bash\n94: # Clone the repository\n95: git clone https://github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube.git\n96: cd agentcube\n97: \n98: # Build the agentcube binary\n99: make build\n100: \n101: # Build Docker images\n102: make docker-build\n103: \n104: # Deploy to local cluster\n105: make deploy-local\n106: ```\n107: \n108: ## SDK Installation\n109: \n110: ### Python SDK\n111: \n112: Install the AgentCube Python SDK:\n113: \n114: ```bash\n115: pip install agentcube-sdk\n116: ```\n117: \n118: Or install from source:\n119: \n120: ```bash\n121: git clone https://github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube.git\n122: cd agentcube/sdk-python\n123: pip install -e .\n124: ```\n125: \n126: Verify installation:\n127: \n128: ```python\n129: import agentcube\n130: print(agentcube.__version__)\n131: ```\n132: \n133: ### Go Client\n134: \n135: Add to your Go project:\n136: \n137: ```bash\n138: go get github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go\n139: ```\n140: \n141: Or import in your code:\n142: \n143: ```go\n144: import \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go\"\n145: ```\n146: \n147: Verify installation:\n148: \n149: ```go\n150: package main\n151: \n152: import (\n153:     \"fmt\"\n154:     \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go\"\n155: )\n156: \n157: func main() {\n158:     client, err := agentcube.NewClient()\n159:     if err != nil {\n160:         panic(err)\n161:     }\n162:     fmt.Println(\"AgentCube client initialized successfully\")\n163: }\n164: ```\n165: \n166: ## Configuration\n167: \n168: ### Environment Variables\n169: \n170: Configure AgentCube behavior with environment variables:\n171: \n172: | Variable | Description | Default |\n173: |----------|-------------|---------|\n174: | `AGENTCUBE_API_ENDPOINT` | API server endpoint | `http://localhost:8080` |\n175: | `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` | Kubernetes namespace | `agentcube-system` |\n176: | `AGENTCUBE_TIMEOUT` | Request timeout (seconds) | `30` |\n177: | `AGENTCUBE_LOG_LEVEL` | Log level (debug, info, warn, error) | `info` |\n178: \n179: Set environment variables:\n180: \n181: ```bash\n182: export AGENTCUBE_API_ENDPOINT=\"http://agentcube-router.agentcube-system.svc.cluster.local:8080\"\n183: export AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE=\"agentcube-system\"\n184: export AGENTCUBE_LOG_LEVEL=\"debug\"\n185: ```\n186: \n187: ### Configuration File\n188: \n189: Create a configuration file `agentcube.yaml`:\n190: \n191: ```yaml\n192: apiEndpoint: http://agentcube-router.agentcube-system.svc.cluster.local:8080\n193: namespace: agentcube-system\n194: timeout: 30\n195: logLevel: info\n196: \n197: sandbox:\n198:   defaultTimeout: 300s\n199:   maxMemoryLimit: 512Mi\n200:   defaultCpuLimit: 500m\n201:   \n202:   podSpec:\n203:     image: python:3.11-slim\n204:     resources:\n205:       requests:\n206:         cpu: 100m\n207:         memory: 128Mi\n208:       limits:\n209:         cpu: 500m\n210:         memory: 512Mi\n211: ```\n212: \n213: Load configuration:\n214: \n215: ```python\n216: from agentcube import Client\n217: \n218: client = Client(config_file=\"agentcube.yaml\")\n219: ```\n220: \n221: ## Verification\n222: \n223: ### Check Installation\n224: \n225: Verify AgentCube is running correctly:\n226: \n227: ```bash\n228: # Check pods\n229: kubectl get pods -n agentcube-system\n230: \n231: # Check services\n232: kubectl get svc -n agentcube-system\n233: \n234: # Check CRDs\n235: kubectl get crd sandboxes.agentcube.io\n236: ```\n237: \n238: ### Test Basic Functionality\n239: \n240: Create a test sandbox:\n241: \n242: ```python\n243: from agentcube import Client\n244: \n245: client = Client()\n246: \n247: session = client.create_session(\n248:     language=\"python\",\n249:     timeout=60\n250: )\n251: \n252: result = session.execute(\"print('Hello, AgentCube!')\")\n253: print(result.output)\n254: \n255: session.close()\n256: ```\n257: \n258: Expected output:\n259: ```\n260: Hello, AgentCube!\n261: ```\n262: \n263: ## Troubleshooting\n264: \n265: ### Common Issues\n266: \n267: **Issue**: Pods not starting\n268: ```\n269: Error: sandbox pods stuck in Pending state\n270: ```\n271: \n272: **Solution**: Check resource quotas and node capacity:\n273: ```bash\n274: kubectl describe pod <pod-name> -n agentcube-system\n275: kubectl top nodes\n276: ```\n277: \n278: **Issue**: Connection refused\n279: ```\n280: Error: connection refused to agentcube-router\n281: ```\n282: \n283: **Solution**: Verify service is running:\n284: ```bash\n285: kubectl get svc agentcube-router -n agentcube-system\n286: kubectl port-forward svc/agentcube-router 8080:8080 -n agentcube-system\n287: ```\n288: \n289: **Issue**: Permission denied\n290: ```\n291: Error: permission denied when creating sandbox\n292: ```\n293: \n294: **Solution**: Check RBAC permissions:\n295: ```bash\n296: kubectl auth can-i create sandboxes.agentcube.io --as=system:anonymous\n297: ```\n298: \n299: ### Debug Mode\n300: \n301: Enable debug logging:\n302: \n303: ```bash\n304: export AGENTCUBE_LOG_LEVEL=debug\n305: kubectl logs -f deployment/agentcube-router -n agentcube-system\n306: ```\n307: \n308: ## Next Steps\n309: \n310: - [Create Your First Sandbox](./first-sandbox.md) - Quick start tutorial\n311: - [Configuration Guide](./configuration.md) - Advanced configuration options\n312: - [Architecture Overview](../architecture/overview.md) - Understand system design\n\n(End of file - total 312 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\nsidebar_position: 1\nid: installation\ntitle: Installation\ndescription: Install AgentCube and set up your development environment\n---\n\n# Installation\n\n## Prerequisites\n\nBefore installing AgentCube, ensure you have the following prerequisites:\n\n### System Requirements\n\n- **Operating System**: Linux, macOS, or Windows with WSL2\n- **Kubernetes**: v1.24+ cluster (minikube, kind, or production cluster)\n- **kubectl**: v1.24+ configured to access your cluster\n- **Helm**: v3.8+ (optional, for Helm deployment)\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/docs/docs/getting-started/installation.md","time":{"start":1775905770873,"end":1775905770905}}}}
